---
import { siteMetadata } from "@config/siteMetadata";
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const meta = {
	title: `Privacy Policy — ${siteMetadata.name}`,
	description: `Privacy policy for greaterphuket.com — what data we collect, why, and your rights under GDPR, CCPA, and other applicable privacy laws.`,
	noindex: true,
};
---

<BaseLayout metaData={meta}>
  <main class="wrapper flow">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: June 2026</em></p>

    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your
      information in compliance with global privacy regulations, including:
    </p>

    <h2>Applicable Privacy Regulations</h2>

    <h3>Europe</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>GDPR</strong> (General Data Protection Regulation, EU)</li>
      <li><strong>UK Data Protection Act 2018</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Americas</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>CCPA</strong> (California Consumer Privacy Act, USA)</li>
      <li><strong>LGPD</strong> (Lei Geral de Proteção de Dados, Brazil)</li>
      <li><strong>PIPEDA</strong> (Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act, Canada)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Asia-Pacific</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Australia Privacy Act 1988</strong></li>
      <li><strong>New Zealand Privacy Act 2020</strong></li>
      <li><strong>PDPA</strong> (Personal Data Protection Act, Singapore)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Africa</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>POPIA</strong> (Protection of Personal Information Act, South Africa)</li>
    </ul>

    <p>We also comply with other applicable international privacy laws in your jurisdiction.</p>

    <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
    <p>
      Greater Phuket is a content website covering travel, lifestyle, and local
      information for Phuket and the surrounding region. If you have any
      questions about this policy, contact us at{" "}
      <a href={`mailto:${siteMetadata.contactEmail}`}>{siteMetadata.contactEmail}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

    <h3>Information Collected Automatically</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Device Information</strong>: Browser type, device type, operating system.</li>
      <li><strong>Usage Data</strong>: Pages visited, time on page, links clicked, referring pages.</li>
      <li><strong>Location Data</strong>: Approximate location derived from your IP address (country/region level only).</li>
      <li><strong>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</strong>: Only with your consent (see Section 7).</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Information You Provide Directly</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Communications</strong>: If you email us directly, we retain your email address and message only for as long as needed to respond.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Website Improvement</strong>: Analysing usage patterns to improve content and performance.</li>
      <li><strong>Personalisation</strong>: Displaying appropriate currency formats based on approximate location (via Netlify geolocation).</li>
      <li><strong>Communication</strong>: Responding to direct enquiries.</li>
      <li><strong>Legal Compliance</strong>: Complying with legal obligations and protecting our rights.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Consent</strong>: Analytics cookies are only set after you accept via the consent banner.</li>
      <li><strong>Legitimate Interests</strong>: To improve our website and respond to direct enquiries.</li>
      <li><strong>Legal Obligation</strong>: To comply with applicable laws.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Third-Party Data Processing</h2>

    <h3>Google Analytics</h3>
    <p>
      With your consent, we use <strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> to
      understand how visitors use the site. It collects pages visited, time on
      page, traffic sources, device type, and approximate geographic location.
      No analytics data is collected until you accept via the cookie banner.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Google's Privacy Policy</strong>:{" "}
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        policies.google.com/privacy
      </a>
    </p>
    <p>
      You can opt out at any time by clearing your browser cookies and declining
      on your next visit, or by installing the{" "}
      <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on
      </a>.
    </p>

    <h3>Pandalytics</h3>
    <p>
      We use <strong>Pandalytics</strong>, our proprietary analytics platform,
      to track page performance and user behaviour. Pandalytics collects:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Page URLs, paths, and referrers.</li>
      <li>Session identifiers and device information (screen size, browser type).</li>
      <li>Approximate location (country code, derived from your IP address).</li>
      <li>Web performance metrics (page load times, Core Web Vitals).</li>
      <li>User agent and browser information.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This data is stored in our database and is used solely to improve website
      performance and user experience. Pandalytics data is retained for up to
      12 months.
    </p>

    <h3>Netlify</h3>
    <p>
      We use <strong>Netlify</strong> for website hosting. Netlify collects
      your IP address to determine your approximate geographic location (country
      code only), which is used to display appropriate currency formats. Server
      logs (IP address, user agent) are retained for up to 30 days. Netlify
      does not retain geolocation data beyond the immediate transaction.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Netlify's Privacy Policy</strong>:{" "}
      <a href="https://www.netlify.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        netlify.com/privacy
      </a>
    </p>

    <h2>6. Your Privacy Rights</h2>

    <h3>Under GDPR (EU residents)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Access</strong>: Obtain a copy of your personal data.</li>
      <li><strong>Rectification</strong>: Correct inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
      <li><strong>Erasure</strong>: Request deletion of your data ("right to be forgotten").</li>
      <li><strong>Portability</strong>: Receive your data in a portable format.</li>
      <li><strong>Objection</strong>: Opt out of processing based on legitimate interests.</li>
      <li><strong>Restrict Processing</strong>: Limit how we use your data.</li>
      <li><strong>Lodge a Complaint</strong>: Contact your local data protection authority.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Under UK GDPR (UK residents)</h3>
    <p>Same rights as EU GDPR above. You may also file a complaint with the <strong>Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</strong>.</p>

    <h3>Under CCPA (California residents)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Know</strong>: What personal information is collected, used, and shared.</li>
      <li><strong>Delete</strong>: Request deletion of personal information.</li>
      <li><strong>Opt-Out</strong>: Opt out of the sale or sharing of personal information. (We do not sell personal information.)</li>
      <li><strong>Non-Discrimination</strong>: We will not discriminate against you for exercising your rights.</li>
      <li><strong>Correct</strong>: Request correction of inaccurate personal information.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Under LGPD (Brazil residents)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Access, correct, and request deletion of your personal data.</li>
      <li>Request clarification about how your data is used.</li>
      <li>File a complaint with the Brazilian Data Protection Authority (ANPD).</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Under PIPEDA (Canada residents)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Access and review your personal information.</li>
      <li>Request correction of inaccurate information.</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent for data collection.</li>
      <li>File a complaint with the Privacy Commissioner of Canada.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Under the Australia Privacy Act 1988</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Access and request correction of your personal information.</li>
      <li>Make a complaint to the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Under the New Zealand Privacy Act 2020</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Access and request correction of your personal information.</li>
      <li>File a complaint with the New Zealand Privacy Commissioner.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Under PDPA (Singapore residents)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Access and correct your personal data.</li>
      <li>Request withdrawal of consent.</li>
      <li>File a complaint with the Personal Data Protection Commission.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Under POPIA (South Africa residents)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Request access, correction, or deletion of your personal information.</li>
      <li>Request restriction of processing.</li>
      <li>File a complaint with the Information Regulator.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How to Exercise Your Rights</h3>
    <p>
      Contact us at{" "}
      <a href={`mailto:${siteMetadata.contactEmail}`}>{siteMetadata.contactEmail}</a>.
      We will respond within 30 days (or as required by applicable law).
    </p>

    <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      We only set analytics cookies after you give consent via the cookie
      banner. No advertising or tracking cookies are used. You can withdraw
      consent at any time by clearing your browser cookies and declining on your
      next visit.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Essential</strong>: Your consent preference is stored in <code>localStorage</code> (not a cookie) and is never shared.</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics</strong>: Google Analytics 4 cookies, set only with consent.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>8. International Data Transfers</h2>
    <p>
      Your data may be transferred to and processed in the United States (Google
      Analytics, Netlify). We rely on Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) as
      the legal mechanism for international data transfers under GDPR.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Data Security</h2>
    <p>
      We use HTTPS encryption for all data in transit, and rely on Netlify's
      secure infrastructure. No method of transmission over the internet is
      100% secure; we cannot guarantee absolute security. In the event of a
      data breach affecting your personal information, we will notify you and
      relevant authorities as required by law.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Data Retention</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong>: Retained for 14 months, then automatically deleted by Google.</li>
      <li><strong>Pandalytics</strong>: Page views and performance metrics retained for up to 12 months.</li>
      <li><strong>Netlify logs</strong>: Retained for up to 30 days.</li>
      <li><strong>Email communications</strong>: Retained only as long as needed to respond, then deleted.</li>
      <li><strong>Consent preference</strong>: Stored in your browser's <code>localStorage</code> until cleared.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy to reflect changes in our practices or legal
      requirements. We will update the "Last updated" date above when we do.
      Continued use of the website after changes constitutes acceptance of the
      updated policy.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For any privacy-related questions, to exercise your rights, or to raise a
      concern:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Email</strong>:{" "}
      <a href={`mailto:${siteMetadata.contactEmail}`}>{siteMetadata.contactEmail}</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      EU residents also have the right to lodge a complaint with their local
      data protection authority. California residents may contact the California
      Attorney General.
    </p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
